        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 5 at 5:16PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 516 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Alvord, or 7 miles northwest of Decatur, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Alvord around 520 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Greenwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
